@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About - OpenHV Web Edition</PageTitle>

<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
            <h1 class="mb-4">About OpenHV</h1>

            <div class="about-section mb-5">
                <h2>What is OpenHV?</h2>
                <p class="lead">
                    OpenHV is an open-source real-time strategy game based on the Hard Vacuum design by Daniel Cook.
                    It's built on the OpenRA engine and features futuristic corporate warfare in a distant future setting.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The game features multiple factions battling for control of resources and territory using advanced
                    technology, mechs, and strategic warfare. OpenHV aims to be a complete, open-content RTS game
                    with no proprietary assets required.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section mb-5">
                <h2>Web Edition</h2>
                <p>
                    This web edition brings the full OpenHV experience to your browser using cutting-edge web technologies.
                    By leveraging WebAssembly and Blazor, we've successfully ported the entire OpenRA engine to run
                    natively in web browsers without compromising on performance or features.
                </p>

                <h4>Key Features:</h4>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li><strong>Full Game Experience:</strong> Complete OpenHV gameplay with all units, buildings, and mechanics</li>
                    <li><strong>Cross-Platform Multiplayer:</strong> Play with desktop users seamlessly</li>
                    <li><strong>No Installation Required:</strong> Runs directly in your browser</li>
                    <li><strong>Mobile Support:</strong> Optimized for touch devices and mobile browsers</li>
                    <li><strong>Progressive Loading:</strong> Smart asset loading for faster startup times</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section mb-5">
                <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <h5>Frontend</h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Blazor WebAssembly</li>
                            <li>WebGL for graphics rendering</li>
                            <li>Web Audio API for sound</li>
                            <li>WebSockets for networking</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <h5>Game Engine</h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li>OpenRA Engine (WebAssembly)</li>
                            <li>.NET 8 Runtime</li>
                            <li>OpenHV Game Logic</li>
                            <li>Custom Web Adaptations</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section mb-5">
                <h2>Development Status</h2>
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <h5 class="alert-heading">Early Development</h5>
                    <p class="mb-0">
                        This web port is currently in early development. While the foundation is in place,
                        many features are still being implemented. We're working through the phases outlined
                        in our development plan to bring you the complete OpenHV experience.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h4>Current Phase: Foundation Setup</h4>
                <div class="progress mb-3">
                    <div class="progress-bar" role="progressbar" style="width: 25%" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
                        Phase 1 of 6
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h5>Completed:</h5>
                <ul class="status-list">
                    <li class="completed">‚úÖ Blazor WebAssembly project setup</li>
                    <li class="completed">‚úÖ Canvas and WebGL initialization</li>
                    <li class="completed">‚úÖ Input handling system</li>
                    <li class="completed">‚úÖ Basic UI framework</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>In Progress:</h5>
                <ul class="status-list">
                    <li class="in-progress">üîÑ OpenRA engine integration</li>
                    <li class="in-progress">üîÑ Asset loading system</li>
                    <li class="pending">‚è≥ Graphics pipeline adaptation</li>
                    <li class="pending">‚è≥ Audio system conversion</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section mb-5">
                <h2>Open Source</h2>
                <p>
                    Like the original OpenHV and OpenRA projects, this web port is completely open source.
                    The code is available for anyone to study, modify, and contribute to.
                </p>
                <div class="d-flex gap-3">
                    <a href="https://github.com/OpenHV/OpenHV" class="btn btn-outline-primary" target="_blank">
                        <i class="bi bi-github"></i> OpenHV Repository
                    </a>
                    <a href="https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA" class="btn btn-outline-primary" target="_blank">
                        <i class="bi bi-github"></i> OpenRA Engine
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section">
                <h2>Credits</h2>
                <p>
                    This web port builds upon the incredible work of the OpenRA and OpenHV development teams.
                    Special thanks to:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>The OpenRA development team for creating the engine</li>
                    <li>The OpenHV team for the game content and mechanics</li>
                    <li>Daniel Cook for the original Hard Vacuum design</li>
                    <li>The WebAssembly and Blazor teams at Microsoft</li>
